<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="562" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,528,1078,1140]" box="[151,528,1113,1140]" pageId="5" pageNumber="562">
<figureCitation box="[151,219,1114,1140]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1699,1724]" captionTargetBox="[161,1416,181,1660]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,181,1673]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 2A–H. Daimachus sudindicus sp. nov., habitus and wings: A–D, brachypterous males, colour variation, dorsal and lateral view; EF, macropterous male, dorsal and lateral view; GH, forewing and hind wing of macropterous male." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3239927/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="562">Figs 2</figureCitation>
A–H, 3M, 4D, 5I–L, 9A–F.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1186,2041]" pageId="5" pageNumber="562">Colouration and structure as in generic description. In some specimens veins marked with brown. Forewing 2.4x as long as wide. Some individuals with hind wings well-developed.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1186,2041]" pageId="5" pageNumber="562">
<emphasis box="[199,365,1258,1284]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="562">Male genitalia</emphasis>
. Pygofer dorsal margin declivous and concave, posterior margin almost truncate, not bilobed. Subgenital plate held vertically, in lateral view broadened posteriorly with rounded apex and with basal transverse suture. Style with anterior part shorter than posterior part, with apex of apophysis broad. Connective with stem as long as arms and with narrow apex. Aedeagus with well-developed dorsal apodeme, aedeagal shaft dorsally curved near base and then strongly anteriorly recurved with two triangular projections, one on dorsal surface near base and another much larger on ventral surface subapically, gonopore apical, shaft apex widened with lateral angles produced and horn-like, held in tubular anterior projection of segment X. Sternite of segment X produced into short posterior and much longer anterior projections.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1186,2041]" pageId="5" pageNumber="562">
<emphasis box="[199,389,1546,1572]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="562">Female genitalia</emphasis>
. Sternite VII more narrowly V-shaped compared to other species (
<figureCitation box="[1126,1217,1546,1572]" captionStart="FIGURES 4" captionStartId="13.[151,275,1787,1814]" captionTargetBox="[166,1426,191,1748]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,181,1763]" captionText="FIGURES 4A–H. Female pregenital sternites and valvulae of species of Daimachus: A–D, sternites VI and VII of (A) D. exemplificatus Distant, (B) D. matheranensis sp. nov., (C) D. robustus sp. nov. and (D) D. sudindicus sp. nov.; E–H, D. exemplificatus (EF) valvulae I and (GH) valvulae II." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3406227/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="562">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
). Valvula II as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Viraktamath &amp; Webb" authorityYear="2019" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Daimachus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="562" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="robustus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="562">D. robustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[262,348,1581,1608]" captionStart="FIGURES 5" captionStartId="14.[151,275,1889,1916]" captionTargetBox="[156,1426,184,1853]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,179,1864]" captionText="FIGURES 5A–L. Valvulae I and II of species of Daimachus: A–D, D. matheranensis sp. nov.; E–H, D. robustus sp. nov. I–L, D. sudindicus sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3406229/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="562">Fig. 5L</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
